==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grammarian
<hw>Gram*ma"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>grammairien</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One versed in grammar,
or the construction of languages; a philologist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ ⟦ldquo⟧The term was used by the classic ancients as a
term of honorable distinction for all who were considered learned in any
art or faculty whatever.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Brande & C.</au></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who writes on, or teaches, grammar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grammarianism</ent>⟦br⟧
